<h4 class="vig">Rights of the Aboriginal Child</h4>
<img src="{{paths.theme}}images/pow-wow-2.jpg" alt="Ojibwae child in regalia">
<p>Under the Great Law of the Anishinabeg, an Anishinaabe child has aboriginal (ascribed) rights.</p>
<p>These are their Rights:</p>

<ul class="unstyled text-small">
<li>To their Name &mdash;  Anishinabe ishinikasoowin</li>
<li>To their Clan &mdash; dodem</li>
<li>To be with the Family &mdash; gutsiimug</li>
<li>To cultural and ceremonial practices &mdash; Anishinabe miiniggisiwin</li>
<li>To their identity &mdash; anishinabewin</li>
<li>To their language &mdash; anishinabemoowin</li>
<li>To a purposeful and zestful life &mdash; mino bimatiziwin</li>
<li>To their ancestral land &mdash; anishinabe akiing</li>
<li>To the lifestyle of the anishinabe &mdash; anishinabechigewin</li>
<li>To a good education &mdash; kinamaatiwin</li>
<li>To protection within the family &mdash; shanawentasoowin</li>
<li>To protection outside the family &mdash; ganawentasoowin</li>
</ul>